Nigerian artiste, Habib Okikiola (Portable) has made an explosive admission. The controversial singer announced that he founded two notorious gangs in Lagos. Portable made the comment while boasting that he was not scared of anyone. In a trending video, he said: “Open your ears and be listening. “Have you heard of Ajah boys, one million boys? I established them.” He added that socialites Samlarry Eletu and Abu Abel knew him back in the day. Ajah boys, one million boys are known for their violent activities across the state. The police at different times arrested a number of members, while some were declared wanted. In late June, Portable reported himself at the Ogun State Police Command headquarters in Eleweran, Abeokuta. The Zazu crooner was invited for assaulting a young man known as DJ Chicken in a viral video.